Other than his discouragement of laptops, I found no issue with O'Connor. He is accessible, entertaining, and understands student concerns and problems. This is a  seminar course so you have to attend most classes, do the readings, and be prepared to talk to succeed. A background in religion prior to taking this class is helpful but not necessary.
Do not use labtops or any sorts of electronic devices during his lectures because he does not like them. He is a good good good professor anyway. I like him so much.
Interesting projects and paper assignments. Prof O'Connor is extremely knowledgeable, witty and charismatic. He is very engaging and easy to undersand. His accent is just so cute! A great experience.
I loved this class. The readings were excellent and the discussion was superb. Professor O'Connor has moved up to be one of my favourite professors during my four year stay at the university.
